'''玛丽·安·沙德'''（Mary Ann Shadd，{{bd|1823年|10月9日|1893年|6月5日}}）是美籍[[加拿大|加拿大]]反奴隶制活动家、记者、出版商、教师和律师。她是[[北美|北美]]第一位黑人女出版商，也是加拿大第一位女出版商 <ref name="Freeman">{{Cite web|title=The Provincial Freeman|url=https://www.archives.gov.on.ca/english/archival-records/interloan/provincial-freeman.aspx|publisher=Archives of Ontario|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120126000215/http://www.archives.gov.on.ca/english/archival-records/interloan/provincial-freeman.aspx|archivedate=January 26, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Mary Ann Shadd Cary (U.S. National Park Service)|url=https://www.nps.gov/people/mary-ann-shadd-cary.htm|accessdate=2020-09-01|work=www.nps.gov|language=en|archive-date=2021-03-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210318205223/https://www.nps.gov/people/mary-ann-shadd-cary.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。玛丽·安·沙德主编的《省立自由人报》（The Provincial Freeman）創辦于1853年。该报在[[安大略省|安大略省]]南部每周出版，倡导加拿大和美国黑人的平等、融合和自我教育<ref>{{Cite web|title=Mary Ann Shadd Cary|url=http://www.biography.com/people/mary-ann-shadd-cary-214141|accessdate=March 15, 2013|publisher=A&E Networks Television|archive-date=2019-01-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190107212646/https://www.biography.com/people/mary-ann-shadd-cary-214141|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=The Black Press|url=http://www.ourfutureourpast.ca/loc_hist/page.aspx?id=3770562|last=Hill|first=Daniel G.|date=Spring–Summer 1982|journal=Polyphony: The Bulletin of the Multicultural History Society of Ontario|accessdate=August 2, 2013|issue=1|volume=4|page=43|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924075901/http://www.ourfutureourpast.ca/loc_hist/page.aspx?id=3770562|archivedate=September 24, 2015}}</ref>。

